⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Zebes
node MET · MET · ⟦Zebes:MET:0af539⟧

WHO   — Zebes — the fortress-world
WHAT  — The world itself — Crateria's surface, Brinstar's overgrowth, Norfair's lava, Maridia's drowned tunnels, the Wrecked Ship, and Tourian's depths — the arena Samus must descend through and survive.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Metroid (1986) & Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the Pirates made this world their stronghold, hiding Mother Brain and the Metroid menace in its deepest chambers; and because to end them, the hunter must go down into the planet and never be sure the planet will let her leave.
HOW   — By acid and lava and water, by labyrinthine caverns and locked doors, by the beasts that nest in every region — and at the end, by coming apart entirely, the whole world detonating as the hunter runs for the surface.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the world that does not want you to leave — and when you have killed my queen, I will die with her and try to take you down with me.

